1
00:01:03,630 --> 00:01:08,260
[Man]
Where can I go from Your Spirit?

2
00:01:08,334 --> 00:01:12,862
Where can I flee
from Your presence?

3
00:01:12,939 --> 00:01:15,407
If I go up to the heavens,

4
00:01:15,475 --> 00:01:17,409
You're there.

5
00:01:17,477 --> 00:01:21,573
If I rise on the wings of the dawn,

6
00:01:21,648 --> 00:01:26,483
if I settle on the far side of the sea,

7
00:01:26,553 --> 00:01:28,783
even there,

8
00:01:28,855 --> 00:01:32,689
Your Hand will guide me.

9
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:36,126
There is no place you can go,

10
00:01:36,196 --> 00:01:39,131
no place you can be,

11
00:01:39,199 --> 00:01:41,030
where you are not in the presence

12
00:01:41,101 --> 00:01:43,797
of the Lord our God.

13
00:01:43,870 --> 00:01:46,430
There is no thought
you can have,

14
00:01:46,506 --> 00:01:49,007
no dream
you can dream,

15
00:01:49,075 --> 00:01:53,771
where the Lord our God
does not see.

16
00:01:53,847 --> 00:01:55,838
If I go up to the heavens,

17
00:01:55,915 --> 00:01:58,748
You are there.

18
00:01:58,818 --> 00:02:02,879
If I rise on the wings of the dawn,

19
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:07,689
if I settle
on the far side of the sea,

20
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:09,819
even there,

21
00:02:09,896 --> 00:02:13,627
Your hand will guide me.

22
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:18,160
If I make my bed in the depths,

23
00:02:18,238 --> 00:02:22,231
You are there.

24
00:02:45,565 --> 00:02:48,830
[bell ringing in distance]

25
00:02:48,902 --> 00:02:50,631
[squeaking]

26
00:02:55,642 --> 00:02:58,372
[keys jingling]

27
00:03:02,682 --> 00:03:05,173
Dorothy? We're back.

28
00:03:10,089 --> 00:03:12,683
[baby crying]

29
00:03:12,759 --> 00:03:14,488
Dorothy?

30
00:03:16,396 --> 00:03:19,194
[baby continues crying]

31
00:03:19,265 --> 00:03:23,395
Naughty baby won't drink its milk!

32
00:03:23,469 --> 00:03:25,528
Jesus!

33
00:03:45,158 --> 00:03:49,254
[crying]

34
00:04:01,841 --> 00:04:06,403
Shh. Shh.

35
00:04:06,479 --> 00:04:10,472
- No, please!
- Calm down.

36
00:04:10,550 --> 00:04:12,848
[crying]

37
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:15,183
[Man]
You see what I mean?

38
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:16,882
Absolutely normal.

39
00:04:35,008 --> 00:04:37,533
Can I have a cigarette?

40
00:04:46,853 --> 00:04:50,220
Things are still very...

41
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:51,848
confused.

42
00:04:51,924 --> 00:04:53,414
There's no rush.

43
00:04:53,493 --> 00:04:55,791
You take all the time you want.

44
00:05:04,170 --> 00:05:06,934
Where should I begin?

45
00:05:07,006 --> 00:05:08,906
You wanted this case.

46
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:13,241
You knew how difficult it would be.

47
00:05:16,149 --> 00:05:18,310
But you still wanted it.

48
00:05:20,553 --> 00:05:22,953
You insisted.

49
00:05:26,459 --> 00:05:29,587
I wanted to go.

50
00:05:29,662 --> 00:05:32,130
I needed to.

51
00:05:34,834 --> 00:05:38,065
I had to get away
before the city smothered me.

52
00:06:25,785 --> 00:06:28,777
[siren in distance]

53
00:08:10,056 --> 00:08:13,048
<i>## [jazz on radio]</i>

54
00:08:20,199 --> 00:08:23,498
[turns up volume]

55
00:08:23,569 --> 00:08:25,434
<i>## [rock on radio]</i>

56
00:08:25,505 --> 00:08:27,302
[honking]

57
00:08:27,373 --> 00:08:29,637
They're riding our backside!

58
00:08:29,709 --> 00:08:31,006
Hurry up!

59
00:08:31,077 --> 00:08:32,408
[tires screeching]

60
00:08:36,415 --> 00:08:39,384
[static on radio]

61
00:08:39,452 --> 00:08:41,317
Hurry up!

62
00:08:41,387 --> 00:08:44,049
- [honking]
- Faster!

63
00:08:44,123 --> 00:08:47,149
Go! Step on it! Step on it!

64
00:08:49,629 --> 00:08:51,494
<i>## [rock on radio]</i>

65
00:08:51,564 --> 00:08:53,623
[honking]

66
00:08:53,699 --> 00:08:56,065
[tires screeching]

67
00:09:18,925 --> 00:09:20,392
Come on, lads.

68
00:09:20,459 --> 00:09:24,520
[chattering]

69
00:09:35,074 --> 00:09:36,837
The Lord giveth,

70
00:09:36,909 --> 00:09:39,036
and the Lord taketh away.

71
00:09:39,111 --> 00:09:40,373
Look over there!

72
00:09:44,984 --> 00:09:49,114
[coughing]

73
00:09:49,188 --> 00:09:52,214
[heaving]

74
00:09:55,695 --> 00:09:58,095
You all right, miss? You're okay?

75
00:10:00,032 --> 00:10:01,556
I wasn't speeding.

76
00:10:01,634 --> 00:10:03,226
There were two cars racing each other.

77
00:10:03,302 --> 00:10:04,394
Racing each other?

78
00:10:04,470 --> 00:10:06,665
An orange and a blue one.

79
00:10:08,674 --> 00:10:11,006
It's hardly a diving watch you've got there.

80
00:10:11,077 --> 00:10:12,567
Let it dry.

81
00:10:12,645 --> 00:10:14,943
It'll tick again in a day or two.

82
00:10:15,014 --> 00:10:17,312
Well, we can't
sit around here all night.

83
00:10:24,657 --> 00:10:27,125
[thunder]

84
00:10:30,396 --> 00:10:33,593
Wait. There's a back entrance.

85
00:10:47,747 --> 00:10:49,681
The psychiatrist.

86
00:10:52,585 --> 00:10:54,815
- Gloria.
- Did you have a bit of an accident, huh?

87
00:10:54,887 --> 00:10:57,014
[laughs]

88
00:10:58,491 --> 00:11:00,288
All right, Colin?

89
00:11:01,894 --> 00:11:03,361
You come with me.

90
00:11:03,429 --> 00:11:05,488
We'll get you dried off.

91
00:11:19,879 --> 00:11:23,110
Here it is. Isn't a suite,
but I hope you'll be comfortable.

92
00:11:23,182 --> 00:11:25,616
I'll maybe get you another blanket.

93
00:11:25,685 --> 00:11:28,711
It's been cold these last few nights.

94
00:11:31,957 --> 00:11:33,754
The heating's been on all day,

95
00:11:33,826 --> 00:11:36,090
so there should be
plenty of hot water.

96
00:11:40,299 --> 00:11:42,164
This is the bathroom.

97
00:11:42,234 --> 00:11:43,701
Should I run a bath for you?

98
00:11:54,580 --> 00:11:57,014
I'll bring you up another towel.

99
00:12:09,295 --> 00:12:12,025
Don't take any notice of the menfolk.

100
00:12:12,098 --> 00:12:14,623
They're decent enough men at heart.

101
00:12:20,206 --> 00:12:21,867
Be back up in a few minutes.

102
00:12:21,941 --> 00:12:23,841
Bring you up a bit of supper.

103
00:12:37,389 --> 00:12:39,050
[sighs]

104
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:46,588
## [electric guitar]

105
00:13:00,012 --> 00:13:02,242
There you are.

106
00:13:02,314 --> 00:13:03,747
Did you sleep well?

107
00:13:03,816 --> 00:13:06,148
Not with an electric guitar
playing over my head all night.

108
00:13:07,820 --> 00:13:09,014
That's funny.

109
00:13:09,088 --> 00:13:12,057
There's no one here but ourselves.

110
00:13:12,124 --> 00:13:14,354
You were maybe dreaming.

111
00:13:14,426 --> 00:13:18,226
[gasps]
It's a lovely day.

112
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:20,128
I'll get you some white pudding.

113
00:13:20,199 --> 00:13:22,463
It's delicious. You'll love it.

114
00:14:00,472 --> 00:14:02,201
How long will it take to fix this?

115
00:14:02,274 --> 00:14:03,263
It's scrap.

116
00:14:03,342 --> 00:14:04,809
Even if we could get the parts,

117
00:14:04,877 --> 00:14:07,107
it would cost more
than the car's worth.

118
00:14:11,383 --> 00:14:12,475
Can I rent a car?

119
00:14:12,551 --> 00:14:15,145
I've only got that pickup over there.

120
00:14:15,221 --> 00:14:19,351
- Is it safe?
- How safe was your BMW?

121
00:14:19,425 --> 00:14:21,416
I'll get you the keys.

122
00:14:27,566 --> 00:14:29,295
[sighs]

123
00:14:58,697 --> 00:14:59,721
You must understand that I'm here

124
00:14:59,798 --> 00:15:02,892
as much as for your sake
as for Dorothy's.

125
00:15:02,968 --> 00:15:04,902
You're already making excuses for her?

126
00:15:04,970 --> 00:15:06,767
I'm trying to find out the truth.

127
00:15:06,839 --> 00:15:09,137
The truth?

128
00:15:09,208 --> 00:15:11,199
The truth is...

129
00:15:11,277 --> 00:15:14,269
you'll find some name for her condition,

130
00:15:14,346 --> 00:15:15,745
and in another couple of years,

131
00:15:15,814 --> 00:15:18,214
she'll be out there abusing
someone else's child,

132
00:15:18,284 --> 00:15:21,344
maybe even her own.

133
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:23,752
Can you tell me
what happened that night?

134
00:15:26,558 --> 00:15:29,220
That was the first time
we used Dorothy as a babysitter.

135
00:15:29,295 --> 00:15:32,924
I had my doubts,
but the pastor said she was all right.

136
00:15:32,998 --> 00:15:35,228
Dorothy? We're back.

137
00:15:37,403 --> 00:15:39,496
Dorothy?

138
00:15:39,571 --> 00:15:43,564
[baby crying]

139
00:15:43,642 --> 00:15:46,736
Naughty baby won't drink its milk!

140
00:15:46,812 --> 00:15:49,110
[baby crying]

141
00:15:49,181 --> 00:15:51,115
Jesus!

142
00:15:52,318 --> 00:15:53,683
He's my baby.

143
00:15:53,752 --> 00:15:55,515
He's my baby. He's my baby!

144
00:15:55,587 --> 00:15:57,350
- Get away from him!
- He's my baby!

145
00:15:58,924 --> 00:16:00,289
[voice deepens]
Hello, shit face!

146
00:16:00,359 --> 00:16:02,088
[whispering]
What have you done?

147
00:16:02,161 --> 00:16:05,289
What have you done?
What have you done!

148
00:16:06,498 --> 00:16:10,093
- Come on. Come on!
- [baby continues crying]

149
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:18,000
Pastor, you gotta
let us on to the mainland.

150
00:16:18,077 --> 00:16:19,567
It's an emergency. Please!

151
00:16:19,645 --> 00:16:21,408
In this case, we'll make an exception.

152
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:23,277
Well, I'll call for assistance.
They'll send a helicopter.

153
00:16:23,349 --> 00:16:26,341
[baby crying]

154
00:16:36,328 --> 00:16:38,694
She's a fuckin' nutcase.

155
00:16:38,764 --> 00:16:42,256
Ask Paul Fallon's son Jake
what he thinks of her.

156
00:16:55,547 --> 00:16:58,539
[seagulls screeching]

157
00:17:32,551 --> 00:17:34,416
Hello, Dorothy.

158
00:17:36,555 --> 00:17:37,579
I'm Dr. Morton,

159
00:17:37,656 --> 00:17:39,749
but you can call me Jane.

160
00:17:44,396 --> 00:17:47,194
You were expecting me, weren't you?

161
00:18:05,684 --> 00:18:08,118
You're very gifted.

162
00:18:15,727 --> 00:18:19,163
Dorothy, we need to talk.

163
00:18:22,334 --> 00:18:23,323
Can I sit here?

164
00:18:33,879 --> 00:18:35,574
You know why I'm here, don't you?

165
00:18:38,417 --> 00:18:39,941
Look, all I want is to listen to you.

166
00:18:40,018 --> 00:18:43,112
I'm not here to judge you,
and I won't make any decisions.

167
00:19:00,539 --> 00:19:01,597
Do you like babies?

168
00:19:03,942 --> 00:19:06,968
What baby?

169
00:19:07,045 --> 00:19:09,605
There was no baby.
I wasn't even there.

170
00:19:13,352 --> 00:19:15,650
I don't want to speak anymore.

171
00:19:17,489 --> 00:19:19,889
Nobody listens to me.

172
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:22,618
Nobody.

173
00:19:22,694 --> 00:19:24,594
I'm listening.

174
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:30,801
And I'll understand you.

175
00:19:30,869 --> 00:19:32,928
Dorothy.

176
00:19:33,005 --> 00:19:34,939
Trust me.

177
00:19:42,114 --> 00:19:45,515
So where were you if you
weren't at the Kearsleys'?

178
00:19:48,287 --> 00:19:50,721
I said my prayers,

179
00:19:50,789 --> 00:19:52,848
and I went to bed.

180
00:19:55,827 --> 00:19:58,227
And I woke up in the morning

181
00:19:58,297 --> 00:20:00,663
in my bed.

182
00:20:04,836 --> 00:20:07,828
Do you remember anything else?

183
00:20:07,906 --> 00:20:10,204
I'm sick of all your questions.

184
00:20:12,644 --> 00:20:14,373
Okay.

185
00:20:16,982 --> 00:20:20,577
Well, why don't we just
swap places, then?

186
00:20:20,652 --> 00:20:22,552
You ask me questions.

187
00:20:22,621 --> 00:20:24,589
[sniffles]

188
00:20:24,656 --> 00:20:26,385
I can ask you questions?

189
00:20:36,468 --> 00:20:38,902
You think she's guilty, don't you?

190
00:20:38,971 --> 00:20:41,838
I'm just doing the first psychological
assessment in this case.

191
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:43,169
Case?

192
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:45,301
This case is a child.

193
00:20:45,377 --> 00:20:46,742
And she has suffered enough.

194
00:20:46,812 --> 00:20:48,404
It's up to the court
to decide what happens.

195
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:51,506
I promise I'll do what's best for her.

196
00:20:56,488 --> 00:20:58,183
[door closes]

197
00:20:59,591 --> 00:21:01,650
[thunder]

198
00:21:05,030 --> 00:21:07,021
"Curiosity.

199
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:10,796
Sin or flaw?"

200
00:21:14,439 --> 00:21:16,703
That's enough now!

201
00:21:16,775 --> 00:21:19,369
Write that out 100 times

202
00:21:19,444 --> 00:21:20,706
and show me in the morning.

203
00:21:20,779 --> 00:21:22,178
Now go!

204
00:21:40,766 --> 00:21:42,063
So you're the doctor, too?

205
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:43,931
I am.

206
00:21:44,002 --> 00:21:46,470
How long have you
been looking after Dorothy?

207
00:21:46,538 --> 00:21:49,632
Not since she was 13.

208
00:22:07,793 --> 00:22:09,260
Healthy child, isn't she?

209
00:22:10,896 --> 00:22:15,026
Here on the island,
we live a clean, healthy life.

210
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:17,898
Our faith shelters us.

211
00:22:17,969 --> 00:22:21,029
I suppose you just failed to notice
her mental illness?

212
00:22:21,106 --> 00:22:24,542
Dorothy is a special child.

213
00:22:24,609 --> 00:22:26,975
There is a place for her
in our community.

214
00:22:27,045 --> 00:22:28,945
Even if she did molest that baby?

215
00:22:29,014 --> 00:22:31,141
It is the Lord's place to judge, not mine.

216
00:22:31,216 --> 00:22:32,649
I'm not here to judge her, either.

217
00:22:32,718 --> 00:22:34,379
I'm here to help her.

218
00:22:34,453 --> 00:22:35,613
And she can be helped.

219
00:22:38,457 --> 00:22:41,824
We have little faith in your science.

220
00:22:41,893 --> 00:22:45,488
How can your science
fathom her pure soul?

221
00:22:45,564 --> 00:22:48,499
One of God's angels.

222
00:22:48,567 --> 00:22:52,162
An angel that might end up in prison.

223
00:23:06,718 --> 00:23:09,881
They're not really fond
of women in here, are they?

224
00:23:09,955 --> 00:23:12,981
It's a very devout community.

225
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:14,958
They take their faith very seriously.

226
00:23:15,026 --> 00:23:16,220
You're not a believer?

227
00:23:16,294 --> 00:23:17,659
Me? No. Jeez.

228
00:23:17,729 --> 00:23:19,094
Had enough of that when I was a kid.

229
00:23:19,164 --> 00:23:20,256
You were born here?

230
00:23:20,332 --> 00:23:22,129
Hmm. And raised.

231
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:26,637
Tried to escape the place,
but this island is like a magnet.

232
00:23:26,705 --> 00:23:28,070
You can't escape.

233
00:23:31,176 --> 00:23:32,268
There you are.

234
00:23:40,452 --> 00:23:42,579
What is it with white food and this island?

235
00:23:42,654 --> 00:23:44,417
Hey, you've only three days of it.

236
00:23:44,489 --> 00:23:45,581
I have to live here.

237
00:23:50,362 --> 00:23:52,296
I saw Dorothy today.

238
00:23:52,364 --> 00:23:54,662
Yeah? How'd it go?

239
00:23:54,733 --> 00:23:55,893
I think she's scared to death.

240
00:23:55,967 --> 00:23:58,299
- Scared of who?
- Don't know.

241
00:24:00,539 --> 00:24:02,530
Herself, maybe.

242
00:24:02,607 --> 00:24:05,132
Self-loathing can be a powerful driver.

243
00:24:05,210 --> 00:24:07,075
Don't stare at her too long there, John.

244
00:24:07,145 --> 00:24:08,476
You know what these shrinks are like.

245
00:24:08,547 --> 00:24:11,380
Wouldn't want her to know
we're thinking about fucking her.

246
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:13,008
- [both laugh]
- Jesus.

247
00:24:14,853 --> 00:24:16,844
[electricity buzzing]

248
00:24:36,708 --> 00:24:39,575
## [electric guitar]

249
00:24:43,014 --> 00:24:45,448
[sighs]

250
00:24:58,630 --> 00:25:00,689
[Pastor]
Dear Lord...

251
00:25:02,834 --> 00:25:04,802
[soft moaning]

252
00:25:04,870 --> 00:25:10,308
...once again we ask You
to shower Your blessings upon us.

253
00:25:11,977 --> 00:25:15,174
Give unto Your servant Dorothy

254
00:25:15,247 --> 00:25:18,808
the warmth of Your divine light.

255
00:25:18,884 --> 00:25:21,182
Let her find the way

256
00:25:21,253 --> 00:25:23,744
through the halls of darkness.

257
00:25:23,822 --> 00:25:27,087
[soft moaning]

258
00:25:27,158 --> 00:25:29,888
Talk to me.

259
00:25:29,961 --> 00:25:33,055
I know you're there, my son.

260
00:25:35,467 --> 00:25:38,868
Say hello to your mother, son.

261
00:25:38,937 --> 00:25:41,963
[soft moaning]

262
00:25:48,179 --> 00:25:50,511
Happy Birthday, son.

263
00:25:57,422 --> 00:26:00,653
Perhaps this is not the time.

264
00:26:00,725 --> 00:26:02,556
I'm sorry, mate.

265
00:26:06,231 --> 00:26:10,133
[tires screech, honking]

266
00:26:10,201 --> 00:26:13,693
<i>## [rock on radio]</i>

267
00:26:21,346 --> 00:26:22,904
[Boy]
Hello!

268
00:26:22,981 --> 00:26:25,609
Janey!

269
00:26:25,684 --> 00:26:28,175
[Girl]
What's up, lying shrink?

270
00:26:28,253 --> 00:26:30,517
[Boy #2]
Hope we're not wakin' you up, eh!

271
00:26:30,589 --> 00:26:32,784
- [all laughing]
- [honking]

272
00:26:32,857 --> 00:26:35,587
[glass breaking]

273
00:26:39,564 --> 00:26:42,397
- [honking]
